University of Sydney is running a pilot of a bridging diploma for Year 11 students at Scot's College . 
  The program allows students to gain entry to university without completing their final year certificate . 
  Tuition, sporting and curricula fees for the private school reportedly top $30,000 . 
  The University of Sydney has run the pilot program with Scot's college . 
  Fears have been raised that the program allows parents to 'buy' their sons entry to the university . 
 